This paper deals with privacy and optimization in a smart meter system, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of dynamic programming to solve the problem suggests that it could also be classified under game theory (cs.GT) or control systems (cs.SY). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in the measurement of privacy and energy cost. Finally, the use of alternative low-complexity energy management policies suggests that it could also be classified under machine learning (cs.LG).
